title: Foundations and Trends in Machine Learning
domain_text: This publication provides high-level tutorials and state-of-the-art reviews on the fundamental algorithmic, theoretical, and statistical aspects of machine learning. It covers core topics such as optimization, computational learning theory, and the mathematical foundations of modern AI architectures.

title: International Journal of Information Management
domain_text: This journal focuses on the management of information systems and the strategic role of information technology in organizational contexts. Research areas include digital transformation, knowledge management, and the socio-technical implications of emerging data technologies.

title: Science Robotics
domain_text: The journal publishes interdisciplinary research on the design, theory, and application of robotics across various scales and environments. Key topics include soft robotics, autonomous navigation, bio-inspired systems, and the integration of artificial intelligence with physical actuators.

title: Nature Machine Intelligence
domain_text: This venue features research in artificial intelligence, machine learning, and robotics, with a specific interest in their cross-disciplinary influence. It explores algorithmic advances alongside the ethical, societal, and scientific impacts of intelligent systems.

title: Computers and Education: Artificial Intelligence
domain_text: The journal explores the intersection of AI technologies and pedagogical practices to enhance learning outcomes and educational environments. Research focuses on adaptive learning systems, intelligent tutoring, and the ethical implementation of AI in formal and informal education.

title: Internet of Things and Cyber-Physical Systems
domain_text: This journal investigates the integration of networked sensors, actuators, and computing systems within physical environments. Its scope covers system architecture, communication protocols, security, and industrial applications of the Internet of Things.

title: IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence
domain_text: This journal publishes foundational research in computer vision, pattern recognition, and the mathematical modeling of machine intelligence. Primary topics include image analysis, statistical learning theory, and the development of algorithms for high-dimensional data processing.

title: IEEE/CAA Journal of Automatica Sinica
domain_text: This journal covers advanced research in control theory, automation, and intelligent systems for complex industrial processes. It emphasizes topics like networked control, robotics, and the application of machine learning in autonomous engineering systems.

title: Annual Review of Control, Robotics, and Autonomous Systems
domain_text: This publication provides systematic reviews and critical syntheses of significant developments in control engineering and robotic mechanisms. It addresses the design, analysis, and implementation of autonomous systems across aerial, terrestrial, and underwater domains.

title: IEEE Transactions on Neural Networks and Learning Systems
domain_text: This journal focuses on the theory, design, and application of neural networks and related learning systems. Research areas include deep learning architectures, biologically inspired models, and reinforcement learning for solving complex computational problems.

title: IEEE Transactions on Fuzzy Systems
domain_text: The journal publishes research on the theory and application of fuzzy logic, approximate reasoning, and systems dealing with uncertainty. It covers fuzzy set theory, hybrid intelligent systems, and their implementation in control, decision-making, and pattern recognition.

title: Foundations and Trends in Robotics
domain_text: This series offers detailed tutorials and monographs on core robotic technologies, including perception, planning, and control systems. It provides comprehensive syntheses of established and emerging topics in mechanical design, sensing, and robotic autonomy.

title: AI Open
domain_text: This open-access journal covers a wide range of topics in artificial intelligence, including data science, machine learning algorithms, and ethical AI development. It serves as a platform for multi-disciplinary research addressing both theoretical innovations and real-world AI applications.

title: Computational Visual Media
domain_text: The journal publishes research in computer graphics, computer vision, and geometric modeling for visual media production. Key research areas include image and video processing, virtual reality, and computational photography.

title: International Journal of Computer Vision
domain_text: This journal covers the mathematical and algorithmic foundations of computer vision and visual perception. Research topics include object recognition, 3D reconstruction, motion analysis, and the integration of machine learning for visual understanding.

title: Radiology: Artificial Intelligence
domain_text: This journal focuses on the application of machine learning and deep learning techniques to medical imaging and clinical radiology. It addresses the development and validation of AI tools for diagnostic support, image segmentation, and predictive health analytics.

title: Artificial Intelligence Review
domain_text: This journal publishes comprehensive surveys and comparative reports across all subfields of artificial intelligence and expert systems. It provides high-level reviews of evolving techniques in machine learning, natural language processing, and autonomous agents.

title: IEEE Transactions on Intelligent Vehicles
domain_text: This journal explores technologies for autonomous driving, advanced driver assistance systems, and connected vehicle infrastructure. Research areas include sensor fusion, path planning, and the safety protocols of intelligent transportation systems.

title: IEEE Transactions on Cognitive Communications and Networking
domain_text: The journal addresses the design and implementation of cognitive radio and AI-driven networking protocols for wireless communications. It focuses on spectrum management, software-defined networks, and the integration of machine learning for network optimization.

title: Physics of Life Reviews
domain_text: This publication focuses on mathematical and physical modeling applied to biological systems and living structures. Research areas include evolutionary dynamics, complex systems theory, and the physical principles underlying biological processes.
